  "chapter": {
    "number": 32,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Elihu Rebukes Job’s Friends"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "So these three men stopped answering Job, because he was righteous in his own eyes."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          "This kindled the anger of Elihu son of Barachel the Buzite, of the family of Ram. He burned with anger against Job for justifying himself rather than God,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          "and he burned with anger against Job’s three friends because they had failed to refute Job, and yet had condemned him."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          "Now Elihu had waited to speak to Job because the others were older than he."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          "But when he saw that the three men had no further reply, his anger was kindled."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          "So Elihu son of Barachel the Buzite declared:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“I am young in years,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "while you are old;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "that is why I was timid and afraid",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to tell you what I know.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I thought that age should speak,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and many years should teach wisdom.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But there is a spirit",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3199
          },
          {
            "text": "in a man,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the breath of the Almighty,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "that gives him understanding.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "It is not only the old",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3200
          },
          {
            "text": "who are wise,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or the elderly who understand justice.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore I say, ‘Listen to me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I too will declare what I know.’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Indeed, I waited while you spoke;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I listened to your reasoning;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "as you searched for words,",
            "poem": 1
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I paid you full attention.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "But no one proved Job wrong;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "not one of you rebutted his arguments.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So do not claim, ‘We have found wisdom;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "let God, not man, refute him.’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But Job has not directed his words against me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and I will not answer him with your arguments.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Job’s friends are dismayed, with no more to say;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "words have escaped them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Must I wait, now that they are silent,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "now that they stand and no longer reply?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I too will answer;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "yes, I will declare what I know.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For I am full of words,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and my spirit within me compels me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Behold, my belly is like unvented wine;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "it is about to burst like a new wineskin.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I must speak and find relief;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I must open my lips and respond.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will be partial to no one,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "nor will I flatter any man.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For I do not know how to flatter,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or my Maker would remove me in an instant.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
